[ Door closes ]

17:08.096 --> 17:09.495
Shit.

17:09.497 --> 17:10.763
Are you hit?

17:10.765 --> 17:12.565
Aah, stop!
Can you breathe?
Come here.

17:12.567 --> 17:14.433
Sit up.
Let's sit you up.

17:14.435 --> 17:16.168
Come on.
Oh, shit.

17:16.170 --> 17:18.971
Jake: Jesus Christ, man.
Talk to me.

17:18.973 --> 17:21.440
What happened?
Who did it?

17:21.442 --> 17:22.641
Pete.

17:22.643 --> 17:23.642
Who's Pete?

17:23.644 --> 17:25.243
Will you get some ice,
please?

17:25.245 --> 17:26.912
No.
Tell me who Pete is.

17:26.914 --> 17:28.581
Or I can.

17:31.519 --> 17:33.719
Who's Pete?

17:33.721 --> 17:35.654
[ Ice cubes clattering ]

17:35.656 --> 17:37.323
Does he owe
somebody money?

17:37.325 --> 17:39.125
Because that's what happens
when you owe somebody money.

17:39.127 --> 17:41.127
It doesn't matter
right now.
Yeah, it<i> does</i>
matter, Jake,

17:41.129 --> 17:43.662
'cause he screwed
our job, okay?

17:43.664 --> 17:45.197
You're gonna tell me
who Pete is.

17:45.199 --> 17:47.333
Jesus Christ, Janine.

17:47.335 --> 17:49.936
Are you kidding me, Jake?

17:49.938 --> 17:51.603
This is gambling,
isn't it?

17:51.605 --> 17:53.272
That's why
you're late for shit.

17:53.274 --> 17:55.407
That's why
you're missing jobs.

17:55.409 --> 17:59.011
Are you calling your bookie
off of my phone in my house,

17:59.013 --> 18:01.280
when you're supposed to be
watching my kid?!

18:01.282 --> 18:03.349
Jake:
Chill out!
Shut up, Jake!

18:06.020 --> 18:08.554
Clean yourself up.

18:08.556 --> 18:10.689
How's your ribs?
Anything broke?

18:10.691 --> 18:14.627
Uh, I'm fine.
Just my face. [ Groans ]

18:14.629 --> 18:16.028
Yeah, you look better.

18:16.030 --> 18:17.696
How much
are you in for?

18:17.698 --> 18:19.398
How much?

18:21.369 --> 18:23.435
Manny: Janine --
Manny!

18:23.437 --> 18:26.272
How much
are you in for?

18:28.308 --> 18:31.043
10 grand.

18:31.045 --> 18:33.512
Ah, shit.

18:33.514 --> 18:35.914
You know
where to find him?

18:35.916 --> 18:37.183
[ Sighs ]

18:37.185 --> 18:38.784
Are you gonna make me
ask around?

18:38.786 --> 18:42.321
Janine, just give it
a second, okay?

18:42.323 --> 18:44.456
We're not gonna leave him here
like this.

18:44.458 --> 18:46.124
Pete did.

18:46.126 --> 18:49.662
Come on.
[ Door opens ]

18:49.664 --> 18:51.631
God damn it.

18:52.667 --> 18:54.000
'Sup, Carlos?

18:54.002 --> 18:56.602
Hey, man. What's up?

18:56.604 --> 18:58.270
Looks good.

18:58.272 --> 18:59.872
Thanks.

18:59.874 --> 19:02.474
Yeah, I heard you're serving
over at Sun of a Beach tonight.

19:02.476 --> 19:04.076
Yeah, they're having
that thing.

19:04.078 --> 19:06.412
So, bring all your shit
over to the Drop instead.

19:06.414 --> 19:07.880
Dude.
They already paid me.

19:07.882 --> 19:10.482
Yeah, Deran'll pay you.
Get paid twice.

19:10.484 --> 19:12.418
And tell whoever else
they roped into this thing

19:12.420 --> 19:14.554
same goes for them, too.

19:17.025 --> 19:18.490
Alright.

19:18.492 --> 19:20.693
Renn gonna be there?

19:20.695 --> 19:21.794
Nah.

19:23.564 --> 19:26.298
Why?
Just looking to re-up.

19:26.300 --> 19:27.633
No, she's done
with that, man.

19:27.635 --> 19:31.303
'Cause I just scored
off of her last week.

19:31.305 --> 19:33.171
Sorry, man. I didn't think
it was a big deal.

19:33.173 --> 19:35.107
Nah. Nah, it's not.

19:35.109 --> 19:37.776
Just make sure everyone's
at Deran's tonight, alright?

19:37.778 --> 19:39.679
Alright. Bet.

19:50.725 --> 19:54.861
[ Dogs barking in distance ]

19:54.863 --> 19:57.263
This is it?

19:57.265 --> 19:59.398
Yeah.

19:59.400 --> 20:01.667
5102 South Nevada.

20:01.669 --> 20:03.870
Doesn't look
like we need a key.

20:06.340 --> 20:18.016
♪♪

20:18.018 --> 20:20.586
[ Debris crunching, scattering ]

20:22.690 --> 20:24.623
Jesus.

20:24.625 --> 20:27.359
Cops, probably.

20:27.361 --> 20:29.428
They use places like this
for drills.

20:29.430 --> 20:31.731
There was one near
my mom's old apartment.

20:33.768 --> 20:36.569
Did he say
where they'd be?
No.

20:39.574 --> 20:41.907
Oh, they're in here.

20:41.909 --> 20:50.783
♪♪

20:50.785 --> 20:59.325
♪♪

20:59.327 --> 21:08.200
♪♪

21:08.202 --> 21:10.303
What is it?

21:13.674 --> 21:15.942
It's Baz's murder file.

21:15.944 --> 21:20.847
♪♪

21:24.151 --> 21:26.151
♪♪

21:26.153 --> 21:27.687
What are you gonna do,
Janine?

21:27.689 --> 21:29.355
Just stay here.

21:29.357 --> 21:38.364
♪♪

21:38.366 --> 21:47.306
♪♪

21:47.308 --> 21:56.315
♪♪

21:56.317 --> 22:05.324
♪♪

22:05.326 --> 22:06.858
Listen to me.

22:06.860 --> 22:08.460
Pete's no joke.

22:08.462 --> 22:11.063
Are you gonna at least
tell me the plan?

22:12.734 --> 22:13.933
What about the kids?

22:13.935 --> 22:15.667
Bree's gonna watch them
all day.

22:15.669 --> 22:17.737
Janine.
Just drive.

22:17.739 --> 22:22.274
♪♪

22:22.276 --> 22:25.010
You know, that Detective Pearce
was all over our asses,

22:25.012 --> 22:27.479
and I don't see shit on him
in here.

22:27.481 --> 22:28.614
Pearce was state.

22:28.616 --> 22:31.083
The Oceanside guys
are Barker and Andre.

22:31.085 --> 22:32.952
What about that DEA guy,
Livengood?

22:32.954 --> 22:35.020
I don't see him
in here, either,

22:35.022 --> 22:36.956
except for a couple, uh,
courtesy heads-up

22:36.958 --> 22:38.490
on surveillance.
That's it.

22:38.492 --> 22:40.459
Yeah, but he's still
out there.

22:44.365 --> 22:46.031
What's up, Craig?

22:46.033 --> 22:48.234
Nothing, man.
I just got some shit on my mind.

22:48.236 --> 22:49.635
You're the one that wanted
to go over all of this.

22:49.637 --> 22:50.836
Yeah, I know.

22:50.838 --> 22:53.105
Okay, well,
just take a seat, please.

22:53.107 --> 22:55.575
All that standing up,
it's annoying.

22:55.577 --> 22:59.445
Deran: Here. These are yours.
Take a look at them.

23:02.116 --> 23:03.715
Craig:
Oh, shit from juvie.

23:03.717 --> 23:07.987
J: Cody known associates.
Pete Trujillo, Tina Trujillo.

23:07.989 --> 23:10.122
Billy's on here.

23:10.124 --> 23:12.658
Another guy
named Jake Dunmore.

23:12.660 --> 23:15.995
You know, that guy Jake
was at Smurf's memorial.

23:17.198 --> 23:20.132
Yo, put that
Baz shit away.

23:20.134 --> 23:21.467
Pope: What's the matter
with you?

23:21.469 --> 23:23.569
I don't want
to see that shit.

23:24.738 --> 23:27.406
Alright, guys, come on.

23:27.408 --> 23:29.408
Let's just chill
for a second.

23:29.410 --> 23:31.076
This cop wants to be
on the payroll.

23:31.078 --> 23:32.878
What do we think?
Hmm?

23:32.880 --> 23:34.213
He came through
with this.

23:34.215 --> 23:36.816
We haven't got
much else.

23:36.818 --> 23:38.818
What do you know
about him?

23:38.820 --> 23:40.219
There's not much
to know.

23:40.221 --> 23:42.354
I asked around.
Nothing weird came up.

23:42.356 --> 23:44.956
I-I don't like cops.
Deran: Yeah. No shit.

23:44.958 --> 23:46.425
How much?

23:46.427 --> 23:49.028
Smurf used to pay cops
a couple grand here and there.

23:49.030 --> 23:52.832
Sure. Why not?

23:52.834 --> 23:55.167
Him giving us a heads-up
on stuff,

23:55.169 --> 23:57.937
it's probably worth
the risk, huh?

24:00.107 --> 24:02.107
Yeah, pay him.

24:02.109 --> 24:10.115
♪♪

24:10.117 --> 24:12.251
Messing with the Trujillos
is a bad idea.

24:12.253 --> 24:14.586
Stay in the car, then.

24:14.588 --> 24:23.929
♪♪

24:23.931 --> 24:25.931
Shit.

24:25.933 --> 24:30.269
♪♪

24:30.271 --> 24:32.471
Which one of you
is Pete?

24:35.476 --> 24:37.943
Think you're in
the wrong place,<i> mija.</i>

24:37.945 --> 24:39.144
Sears is up the road.

24:39.146 --> 24:42.214
Oh, I know where I am.

24:42.216 --> 24:44.816
[ Chuckles ]
You're Manny's friend.

24:44.818 --> 24:46.151
How's he doing?

24:46.153 --> 24:49.021
Somebody tuned him up
pretty good.

24:49.023 --> 24:51.156
I'll talk to you.

24:51.158 --> 24:53.092
But Manny's friend stays
right here.

24:53.094 --> 24:55.094
That's fine by me.

24:55.096 --> 24:57.997
Shoot this asshole
if he does anything stupid.

25:00.568 --> 25:01.968
Junior.

25:14.782 --> 25:17.316
[ Sighs ]

25:17.318 --> 25:19.184
So, you Manny's chick
or something?

25:19.186 --> 25:21.921
Smurf: No.
Didn't think so.

25:21.923 --> 25:24.123
[ Clicks tongue ]
Too pretty.

25:30.532 --> 25:32.197
Well, look at you.

25:32.199 --> 25:34.367
That's 10 grand.

25:38.272 --> 25:42.674
So, if Manny's not
your<i> vato...</i>

25:42.676 --> 25:44.476
why you paying for him?

25:44.478 --> 25:46.478
Are we good?
For now.

25:46.480 --> 25:49.749
But if Manny wants to play,
he's got to pay.

25:49.751 --> 25:52.684
And we both know he's gonna be
underwater with me

25:52.686 --> 25:53.819
in three weeks tops.

25:53.821 --> 25:57.022
Gonna keep footin' his bill
for him?

25:57.024 --> 25:58.890
He's not coming back.

25:58.892 --> 26:01.761
[ Laughs ]

26:01.763 --> 26:03.362
Damn!

26:03.364 --> 26:05.697
She'd give your [speaking
Spanish] a run for her money,

26:05.699 --> 26:07.166
<i> que no, mijo?</i>

26:07.168 --> 26:09.635
<i> Destructor de bolas.</i>

26:11.973 --> 26:13.172
Hey,<i> mija, mija.</i>

26:13.174 --> 26:14.506
You got all this money,

26:14.508 --> 26:17.709
talking about keeping
grown men in line.

26:17.711 --> 26:19.845
What the hell is it
that you do?

26:19.847 --> 26:24.116
I look for opportunities.

26:24.118 --> 26:26.252
[ Snaps fingers ]
I like you.

26:30.524 --> 26:34.059
You sell anything here
aside from cars?

26:34.061 --> 26:35.995
What do you need?

26:35.997 --> 26:38.130
[ Chuckles ]

26:40.734 --> 26:42.768
What can you get?

26:52.079 --> 27:03.489
[ Engine shuts off ]

27:03.491 --> 27:06.558
Renn?

27:06.560 --> 27:08.327
Yo, Renn.

27:58.612 --> 28:00.213
[ Sighs ]

28:02.216 --> 28:03.583
Shit.

28:05.753 --> 28:15.427
♪♪

28:15.429 --> 28:25.170
♪♪

28:25.172 --> 28:27.039
The files are back
where we found them.

28:27.041 --> 28:29.175
Excellent.

28:32.313 --> 28:33.979
One grand a month.

28:33.981 --> 28:37.583
I'm worth more
than that.

28:37.585 --> 28:39.585
That's twice
what Barker got.

28:39.587 --> 28:42.187
That's a pretty low bar,
don't you think?

28:42.189 --> 28:48.594
♪♪

28:48.596 --> 28:51.731
Okay.

28:51.733 --> 28:54.066
I know more than
what's in those files.

28:54.068 --> 28:55.267
Like what?

28:55.269 --> 28:57.603
Like the DEA's
up your ass.

28:57.605 --> 28:59.338
DEA doesn't have
shit on us.

29:00.074 --> 29:02.674
Well, I'd call aiding and
abetting a fugitive something,

29:02.676 --> 29:06.478
but hey...
tomato, tomahto.

29:06.480 --> 29:09.415
One of you is sending money
to Indonesia.

29:12.686 --> 29:16.622
Livengood's using it as probable
cause, shopping judges.

29:16.624 --> 29:19.024
Maybe he gets lucky,
maybe not.

29:19.026 --> 29:22.395
But you'd want to know before
he drops a warrant, right?

29:26.100 --> 29:27.700
Two grand.

29:28.970 --> 29:30.102
One five.

29:30.104 --> 29:32.705
There's a thousand there.
We'll get you the rest.

29:35.109 --> 29:37.176
Do that.

29:37.178 --> 29:38.910
And stop sending money.

29:38.912 --> 29:40.846
[ Engine starts ]

29:40.848 --> 29:47.186
♪♪

29:47.188 --> 29:50.856
You're sending money
to Adrian?

29:50.858 --> 29:52.324
No, I'm not.

29:52.326 --> 29:54.227
Who, then?

29:56.931 --> 29:58.798
I'll take care of it.

29:58.800 --> 30:00.433
[ Engine starts ]

30:10.945 --> 30:13.078
[ Engine shuts off ]

30:13.080 --> 30:19.551
♪♪

30:19.553 --> 30:25.957
♪♪

30:25.959 --> 30:28.961
[ Speaking Spanish ]

30:31.833 --> 30:34.433
[ Door opens ]

30:34.435 --> 30:44.776
♪♪

30:44.778 --> 30:55.120
♪♪

30:55.122 --> 30:58.257
Babe?

30:58.259 --> 31:01.327
So, did Nick actually have
a doctor's appointment today,

31:01.329 --> 31:04.030
or is that just
filled with cash?

31:05.867 --> 31:07.867
You're dealing again?

31:07.869 --> 31:09.601
Yeah.
In Oceanside?

31:09.603 --> 31:11.136
Well, that's where I live,
isn't it?
After I asked you
not to?

31:11.138 --> 31:12.804
I knew you'd be a dick
about it.

31:12.806 --> 31:14.206
What'd you do with all the cash
I gave you this morning?

31:14.208 --> 31:15.741
Diapers! Food!
Oh, any drugs?

31:15.743 --> 31:17.276
That's not even
what this is about!
Anything else you doing?

31:17.278 --> 31:18.477
Craig:
What is this about?

31:18.479 --> 31:20.346
This is about me
making my own money!

31:20.348 --> 31:22.281
Well, then go get a real job
like real people.

31:22.283 --> 31:24.550
Oh, like you? You don't even
know what that is.

31:24.552 --> 31:26.218
I do this so that
you don't have to do this!

31:26.220 --> 31:27.953
Oh, whatever!
You've always known who I am!

31:27.955 --> 31:29.355
Yeah.
[ Baby crying ]

31:29.357 --> 31:31.190
But I didn't know you'd also be
a shitty mother.

31:33.094 --> 31:34.960
'Cause Smurf was
such a great one.

31:34.962 --> 31:36.295
Don't you bring her
into this.

31:36.297 --> 31:37.563
Oh, really?
I finally understand her --

31:37.565 --> 31:39.231
Where the hell
you going?

31:39.233 --> 31:40.900
[ Crying continues ]

31:40.902 --> 31:42.668
Get out of my way.

31:52.046 --> 31:53.646
[ Engine shuts off ]

32:02.123 --> 32:04.056
[ Bells jingle ]

32:04.058 --> 32:06.458
[ Man singing in Spanish ]

32:06.460 --> 32:08.794
[ Indistinct conversations ]

32:08.796 --> 32:18.003
♪♪

32:18.005 --> 32:27.146
♪♪

32:27.148 --> 32:36.555
♪♪

32:36.557 --> 32:38.391
Andrew.

32:42.696 --> 32:45.297
I told my CHIPS buddy that
we used to shoot hoops, okay?

32:45.299 --> 32:48.700
So how about you shake my hand
and I sit down?

32:48.702 --> 32:55.174
♪♪

32:55.176 --> 32:56.676
Ahh!

33:00.047 --> 33:01.380
You following me?

33:01.382 --> 33:03.048
I'm just hungry.

33:03.050 --> 33:05.651
Well, chili verde plate.

33:05.653 --> 33:08.053
Trust me.

33:08.055 --> 33:09.855
Why you want to do this?

33:09.857 --> 33:10.790
Excuse me?

33:10.792 --> 33:13.392
Why do you want to work
with my family?

33:13.394 --> 33:17.529
Public service is overrated
and underpaid.

33:17.531 --> 33:20.399
There's easier ways
to make money.

33:20.401 --> 33:22.468
Working security at Coachella
when I'm off-duty

33:22.470 --> 33:24.637
is not really my thing.

33:26.540 --> 33:28.608
Anyway,
you look good.

33:31.613 --> 33:33.479
You were pretty out of it
when we found you

33:33.481 --> 33:37.617
wandering around
that trailer park.

33:37.619 --> 33:39.885
I'm good now.

33:39.887 --> 33:42.554
Okay, great.

33:42.556 --> 33:44.756
So, do we have
a problem?

33:44.758 --> 33:46.526
[ Sighs ]

33:50.898 --> 33:53.032
I'm telling you.

33:53.034 --> 33:55.301
Chili verde plate.

33:55.303 --> 33:57.236
I wouldn't
steer you wrong.

33:57.238 --> 34:02.308
♪♪

34:02.310 --> 34:04.143
[ Knock on door ]

34:10.184 --> 34:12.585
Hey. Come on in.

34:17.659 --> 34:20.059
Thank you for seeing me
on a Saturday.

34:20.061 --> 34:23.929
Yeah, it's easier than trying
a time during the week.

34:23.931 --> 34:26.265
Um, this is for you.

34:26.267 --> 34:30.202
Thank you.

34:30.204 --> 34:32.338
So, you decided
to make a break for it?

34:32.340 --> 34:33.472
It's a retainer.

34:33.474 --> 34:35.875
For future services
for our family.

34:35.877 --> 34:38.477
We also need the name
of a criminal attorney.

34:38.479 --> 34:41.280
Someone with
federal experience.

34:41.282 --> 34:43.415
It's just a precaution.

34:43.417 --> 34:45.150
Okay.
You want some?

34:45.152 --> 34:46.352
No, thank you.

34:46.354 --> 34:47.953
So, future services?

34:47.955 --> 34:50.489
We want to expand
our family business,

34:50.491 --> 34:52.624
and we need someone
who can help us

34:52.626 --> 34:54.159
when we need to be
creative.

34:54.161 --> 34:56.228
Creative?
Yeah.

34:56.230 --> 35:00.233
And you know Smurf's estate
better than anyone, so...

35:02.370 --> 35:04.704
I'm a legit attorney.

35:04.706 --> 35:08.840
So, you're telling me that
everything you do for your
grandma is on the books?

35:08.842 --> 35:11.110
She keeps me out of it.
I don't believe you.

35:11.112 --> 35:14.646
Yeah, well, that's my grandma.
She raised me.

35:14.648 --> 35:16.716
But you, I don't know.
'Cause a little while ago,

35:16.718 --> 35:19.651
you were asking me
how to carve up family assets

35:19.653 --> 35:22.388
so you can get out.

35:22.390 --> 35:24.656
So, what's changed?

35:24.658 --> 35:26.592
We worked it out.

35:26.594 --> 35:29.261
Is that -- Is that
what happened to your face?

35:29.263 --> 35:32.198
Are you always this inquisitive
with your clients?

35:32.200 --> 35:34.467
Eh, just the criminals.

35:36.337 --> 35:37.403
It's a joke.

35:37.405 --> 35:38.870
Are you interested?

35:38.872 --> 35:42.541
You were experiencing a bit of
a cash flow problem before.

35:42.543 --> 35:44.343
You gonna be able
to keep paying me?

35:44.345 --> 35:46.478
That won't be a problem.
Okay.

35:46.480 --> 35:49.881
Well, I got one more
question for you.

35:49.883 --> 35:51.216
What?

35:51.218 --> 35:52.685
Do you ever smile?

35:57.091 --> 36:00.960
When can you get us the names
of a few criminal attorneys?

36:00.962 --> 36:03.028
[ Chuckles ]

36:03.030 --> 36:06.898
Um...I just got to make a few
calls, find a good fit.

36:06.900 --> 36:08.768
So, yeah.

36:08.770 --> 36:11.604
I'll reach out to you
next week.
Okay.

36:13.707 --> 36:15.842
[ Indistinct conversations ]

36:22.383 --> 36:26.051
What are you doing here?

36:26.053 --> 36:27.587
We need to talk.

36:27.589 --> 36:29.855
No.

36:29.857 --> 36:31.657
[ Scoffs ]

36:31.659 --> 36:33.826
Say what you need to say.

36:36.664 --> 36:39.365
You sending money
to Adrian?

36:44.138 --> 36:47.739
How did you find out?

36:47.741 --> 36:52.144
The DEA agent that was trying
to put Adrian in jail.

36:52.146 --> 36:55.147
What did you tell him?

36:55.149 --> 36:56.816
Nothing.

36:56.818 --> 36:59.418
But he's gonna connect the dots
back to you at some point.

36:59.420 --> 37:01.553
The guy I use
is untraceable.

37:01.555 --> 37:04.356
There's, like,
this whole system.

37:04.358 --> 37:05.491
What guy?

37:05.493 --> 37:08.560
Guy over at
the liquor store on Ditmar.

37:08.562 --> 37:11.163
Jesus, Jess, the liquor store?
Come on.

37:11.165 --> 37:12.764
I give him cash,

37:12.766 --> 37:14.766
his connection in Jakarta
gives Adrian the money.

37:14.768 --> 37:16.702
There's no trace.
The guy in Jakarta

37:16.704 --> 37:18.904
doesn't even know my name.
Anybody's name.

37:18.906 --> 37:21.641
Well, the DEA knows
you're sending money,
so you gotta stop.

37:21.643 --> 37:24.443
And abandon him,
like you?

37:26.047 --> 37:28.780
What was your plan,
by the way?

37:28.782 --> 37:32.852
Have Adrian learn Indonesian?
Teach surf lessons?

37:32.854 --> 37:36.188
Shape boards for tourists?
Start running drugs again?

37:36.190 --> 37:38.524
I gave him plenty of money
to get set up down there.

37:38.526 --> 37:40.326
Yeah, and then what?

37:40.328 --> 37:43.329
I don't know.

37:43.331 --> 37:44.930
This isn't my fault.

37:44.932 --> 37:47.399
Your brother got into all that
drug trafficking bullshit

37:47.401 --> 37:48.467
on his own.

37:48.469 --> 37:51.704
Yeah. Sure. [ Scoffs ]

37:55.877 --> 37:59.078
Just stop sending
money, okay?

37:59.080 --> 38:02.414
That a threat?

38:02.416 --> 38:04.684
Yeah.

38:04.686 --> 38:06.952
But not from me.
From the DEA.

38:06.954 --> 38:11.357
They're gonna charge you
and then put you in jail.

38:11.359 --> 38:13.759
Adrian loved you.

38:13.761 --> 38:16.228
He believed in you.

38:16.230 --> 38:21.233
♪♪

38:21.235 --> 38:23.369
That's over now.

38:23.371 --> 38:31.611
♪♪

38:53.334 --> 38:56.535
[ Knocking ]
Hey.

38:56.537 --> 38:57.737
What's up?

38:57.739 --> 39:01.873
I, uh, heard you
making some noise earlier.

39:01.875 --> 39:05.677
I got some new stuff.

39:05.679 --> 39:08.280
Yeah, it looks good
in here.

39:08.282 --> 39:11.150
You doing some demo work?

39:11.152 --> 39:12.752
Oh, the bathroom.

39:12.754 --> 39:16.888
I'm gonna take all that
old Smurf shit out.

39:16.890 --> 39:19.025
Only take a couple days.

39:23.230 --> 39:27.633
Look, I'm sorry you had to
come back to all this shit.

39:27.635 --> 39:30.436
What do you mean?

39:30.438 --> 39:33.505
The DEA. Livengood.

39:33.507 --> 39:35.174
It's...

39:35.176 --> 39:37.309
It's my fault.

39:37.311 --> 39:38.377
What?

39:38.379 --> 39:40.712
I should have done what needed
to be done with Adrian.

39:40.714 --> 39:43.915
I know that.

39:43.917 --> 39:46.518
That's bullshit.

39:46.520 --> 39:48.320
Come on.

39:48.322 --> 39:50.556
That's not you.

39:55.329 --> 39:57.029
Yeah.

40:01.803 --> 40:04.870
I gotta go to the bar,
but, you know, if you want to

40:04.872 --> 40:07.873
come by later for a drink
or something...

40:07.875 --> 40:12.277
Nah, I'm gonna
get some sleep.

40:12.279 --> 40:13.913
Alright.

40:17.418 --> 40:22.488
♪♪

40:22.490 --> 40:24.624
[ Indistinct conversations ]

40:24.626 --> 40:31.297
♪♪

40:31.299 --> 40:37.969
♪♪

40:37.971 --> 40:40.572
Hey, man,
take those shirts off.

40:40.574 --> 40:42.041
Both of you.

40:42.043 --> 40:43.975
Sorry, dude. I forgot.
They were giving out --

40:43.977 --> 40:47.647
Yeah, I know, man.
Just put that shit
on the table, alright?

40:47.649 --> 40:53.519
♪♪

40:53.521 --> 40:59.191
♪♪

40:59.193 --> 41:01.260
Yo. This it?

41:01.262 --> 41:05.264
There's a bunch of people
in the back.

41:05.266 --> 41:07.933
Find us a cop?

41:07.935 --> 41:10.670
Want to say that a little louder
so everybody can hear you, man?

41:10.672 --> 41:12.772
Oh, please, man.
No one gives a shit.

41:15.809 --> 41:17.476
What's going on?

41:17.478 --> 41:20.412
Well, Renn left
and took Nick.

41:20.414 --> 41:22.348
What?

41:22.350 --> 41:24.216
Yeah, we had a fight.

41:24.218 --> 41:25.685
Mm. What about?

41:25.687 --> 41:27.819
It doesn't matter, man.

41:27.821 --> 41:29.821
Well, she'll come back.

41:29.823 --> 41:32.157
[ Sighing ]
Yeah, I don't know.

41:32.159 --> 41:34.093
No, you guys have
a kid together.
She'll come back.

41:34.095 --> 41:37.162
Yeah, but you didn't see
the look on her face.

41:37.164 --> 41:44.236
♪♪

41:44.238 --> 41:48.374
Craig: Well,
look who showed up.

41:48.376 --> 41:51.176
Nice...

41:51.178 --> 41:53.245
party.

41:53.247 --> 41:54.914
You stole
my food vendor guy.

41:54.916 --> 41:57.383
The carnitas
are a hit.

41:57.385 --> 42:00.519
Yeah, come on, L.A.

42:00.521 --> 42:03.723
For the community, right?

42:03.725 --> 42:06.325
I wasn't sure if you wanted
that pile of shirts over there,

42:06.327 --> 42:08.660
but, uh, if not, we're gonna
use them as bar rags.

42:08.662 --> 42:09.861
Parker:
What's your deal, man?

42:09.863 --> 42:11.663
Can't handle the competition?

42:11.665 --> 42:13.065
We know he can't.

42:13.067 --> 42:14.466
That's why
he never went pro.

42:14.468 --> 42:15.601
I get it. That's --

42:15.603 --> 42:18.538
That's what all these broken
boards are about, right?

42:18.540 --> 42:20.840
It's a metaphor.

42:22.544 --> 42:24.543
[ Grunting ]

42:24.545 --> 42:34.820
♪♪

42:34.822 --> 42:45.230
♪♪

42:45.232 --> 42:55.307
♪♪

42:55.309 --> 42:57.810
How you like that metaphor,
bitch?

42:59.447 --> 43:01.347
[ Door opens ]

43:04.918 --> 43:06.718
Oh, good.
You're awake.

43:06.720 --> 43:08.254
Hey, baby.

43:09.256 --> 43:10.990
Jake:
How you feeling?

43:10.992 --> 43:12.391
[ Door closes ]

43:12.393 --> 43:13.993
[ Groaning ] Like shit.

43:13.995 --> 43:16.462
We brought chicken.

43:16.464 --> 43:18.731
And medicine.

43:21.803 --> 43:23.469
What do you think?

43:23.471 --> 43:26.005
Can you eat something?

43:26.007 --> 43:29.141
Did you guys see Pete?
Uh-huh.

43:29.143 --> 43:33.078
W-What'd he say?

43:33.080 --> 43:36.115
[ Sighs ] He's not gonna
bother you anymore.

43:41.422 --> 43:43.356
She paid him.

43:50.832 --> 43:54.766
♪♪

43:54.768 --> 43:56.902
Come here. Eat.

43:56.904 --> 44:01.907
♪♪

44:01.909 --> 44:04.576
[ Groans ]

44:04.578 --> 44:14.453
♪♪

44:14.455 --> 44:15.655
Thank you.

44:15.657 --> 44:18.257
Oh, you don't have to
thank me, baby.

44:18.259 --> 44:20.726
We look out
for each other.

44:20.728 --> 44:28.267
♪♪

44:28.269 --> 44:31.337
You can pay me back
later.

44:31.339 --> 44:41.347
♪♪

44:41.349 --> 44:43.082
[ Glasses clink ]

44:47.555 --> 44:48.888
Here we go, guys.

44:48.890 --> 44:50.389
Thanks, bud.

44:53.895 --> 44:57.296
Hey.
Great party, man.

45:00.634 --> 45:01.967
[ Broken glass scraping ]

45:01.969 --> 45:04.103
No, no, no.
Don't worry about it.

45:04.105 --> 45:06.972
We'll get that.
We'll clean up later.

45:06.974 --> 45:08.374
You can go home.

45:08.376 --> 45:09.508
Catch you guys.

45:09.510 --> 45:11.977
Yeah, man.
Yep.
See you tomorrow.

45:11.979 --> 45:15.447
My hand.
Ugh, this sucks, man.

45:15.449 --> 45:17.116
That's 'cause you're finally
sobering up.

45:17.118 --> 45:19.251
How about you, uh, pour us
a couple more shots?

45:19.253 --> 45:21.521
Jesus.
Way ahead of you.

45:21.523 --> 45:24.056
Hey, you missed it,
bud.

45:24.058 --> 45:27.393
I found us an attorney.

45:27.395 --> 45:29.929
Really?
Mm-hmm.

45:29.931 --> 45:32.398
Nice.
[ Glasses clinking ]

45:32.400 --> 45:34.066
Cheers, fellas.

45:34.068 --> 45:42.674
♪♪

45:42.676 --> 45:51.016
♪♪

45:51.018 --> 45:59.492
♪♪

46:06.634 --> 46:15.240
♪♪

46:15.242 --> 46:23.582
♪♪

46:23.584 --> 46:32.091
♪♪
